Scott Boilen


Posted on October 30, 2014September 22, 2016 by Interact Marketing 


 
30
Oct



 Scott Boilen is the CEO of Allstar Products Group and the man behind the famous Snuggie: the blanket with sleeves. Scott Boilen has worked tirelessly to ensure a stable leadership position for Allstar in the consumer brand space. Boilen has been quoted as saying “I am positive that we have assembled a strong, effective team of specialists who, when combined, are so much more than the sum of their parts. It is rewarding to say with confidence that we have a first-class team.”
It is the network of individuals, with Scott Boilen as CEO, that sets Allstar Marketing apart as a leader in a variety of product categories (including Hardware, Housewares, Pet, Beauty, and more). Scott Boilen, and his team, prove time and again that the DRTV success of Snuggie was not a fluke, but rather the result of combining a strong leadership team with a savvy support staff.

After speaking with Scott Boilen, you can’t help but share his enthusiasm. Boilen explains, “We exist to find, support and bring solutions to market. We vibe off your genius. Put simply, your success is the fuel to our fire.” Scott Boilen is passionate about products and constantly seeks to learn, listen and take advice from product inventors directly. Scott will be the first to admit that, “the inventors often know what works and what doesn’t. Their products are their babies and it is our job to respect and support those positions.” The Allstar leadership team – led by Scott Boilen – often helps an inventor’s dream to become a reality.
In addition to his leadership at Allstar Products Groups, Scott Boilen serves on the Board of Directors for the Electronic Retailing Association and the Board of Directors for the Food Bank for Westchester (New York). Boilen holds a Bachelors degree in Business Administration from State University of New York at Albany and a Master’s Degree in Business Administration from Fordham University.


